<blockquote class="callout">
  <h2 id="if-youre-using-linux--mac--unix">If youâ€™re using Linux / Mac / Unix</h2>

  <p>$ ssh login_name@###.###.###.###</p>

  <p>or (if you have more than one private key)</p>

  <p>$ ssh â€“i ~/.ssh/My_Key_Pair.pem login_name@###.###.###.###</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote class="callout">
  <h2 id="if-youre-using-windows">If youâ€™re using Windows</h2>

  <p>1) Open Putty</p>

  <p>2) Under â€œHost name (or IP address)â€ put: login_name@###.###.###.###</p>

  <p>3) In the menu on the left, expand â€œSSHâ€ and click on â€œAuthâ€.</p>

  <p>4) Under the section â€œAuthentication parametersâ€ click on â€œBrowseâ€¦â€.</p>

  <p>5) Select your previously create .ppk private key.</p>

  <p>6) Click on â€œOpenâ€ to start the connection to your instance.</p>
</blockquote>

